title: analysis
pid: 2bdfe511-8740-4bc5-a775-58b616f353d7
body: |2-
  What's happening is that to find whether someone is in a list
  requires walking through the list.
  If the list is long, that takes a long time --
  and you're doing it for each person in the other list. 

  processing time ~ pop size * group length

  Multiplying both things on the right hand side by 1000
  multiplies the left hand side by 1 million.
